\define ref(content:"empty")
<$macrocall $name="strex" content="""$content$""" label="&#x200b;" start="start" end="&#x200b;" class="hint numbers"/> 
\end
\define strex(content:"TextStretch", label:"…", start:">", end:"close", class:"", id:"_false_")
<$vars content="""$content$""" id="""$id$""">
<$set name="uid" filter="[<id>!prefix[_false_]]" value=<<id>> emptyValue=<<content>> >
<span class="strex-container $class$"><$macrocall $name="strexx" content=<<content>> label="""$label$""" start="""$start$""" end="""$end$""" class="""$class$""" uid=<<uid>>/></span>
</$set>
</$vars>
\end

\define strexx(content, label, start, end, class, uid)
<$set name="xuid" filter="[<uid>prefix[_false_]]" value="error: xuid hashing" emptyValue=<<HashStr """$uid$""">> >
<$macrocall $name="strexxx" content="""$content$""" label="""$label$""" start="""$start$""" end="""$end$""" class="""$class$""" xuid=<<xuid>>/>
</$set>
\end

\define strexxx(content, label, start, end, class, xuid)
<$vars content="""$content$""" label="""$label$""" start="""$start$""" end="""$end$""" class="""$class$""" xuid="""$xuid$""">
<$set name="qualstate" value=<<qualify "$:/state/strex_$xuid$_">> >
<$vars openclass="strex-open $class$" contentclass="strex-content $class$" startclass="strex-close strex-start $class$" endclass="strex-close strex-end $class$">
<$reveal type="nomatch" state=<<qualstate>> text="visible" animate="yes"><$button set=<<qualstate>> setTo="visible" class=<<openclass>> tooltip="show text part"><<label>></$button></$reveal><$reveal type="match" state=<<qualstate>> text="visible" animate="yes">
<span class="strex-all $class$"><span class="strex-inner $class$"><$button set=<<qualstate>> setTo="hidden" class=<<startclass>> tooltip="hide text part">$start$<$action-setfield $tiddler=<<qualstate>>/></$button><span class=<<contentclass>> > <<content>> </span></span><$button set=<<qualstate>> setTo="hidden" class=<<endclass>> tooltip="hide text part">$end$<$action-setfield $tiddler=<<qualstate>>/></$button></span></$reveal>
</$vars>
</$set>
</$vars>
\end

/*\
title: $:/core/modules/macros/HashStr.js
type: application/javascript
module-type: macro

Generate a numeric hash from a string
uses $:/core/modules/utils/utils.js
\*/

(function(){
   /*jslint node: true, browser: true */
   /*global $tw: false */
   "use strict";

/*
Information about this macro
*/
   exports.name = "HashStr";
   exports.params = [
      {name: "str"}
   ];

/*
Run the macro
*/
   exports.run = function(str) {
      var hash = $tw.utils.hashString(str);
      return hash;
   };
})();

            "title": "$:/language/Help/rendertiddlers",
            "description": "Render tiddlers matching a filter to a specified ContentType",
            "text": "Render a set of tiddlers matching a filter to separate files of a specified ContentType (defaults to `text/html`) and extension (defaults to `.html`).\n\n```\n--rendertiddlers <filter> <template> <pathname> [<type>] [<extension>] [\"noclean\"]\n```\n\nFor example:\n\n```\n--rendertiddlers [!is[system]] $:/core/templates/static.tiddler.html ./static text/plain\n```\n\nBy default, the pathname is resolved relative to the `output` subdirectory of the edition directory. The `--output` command can be used to direct output to a different directory.\n\nAny files in the target directory are deleted unless the ''noclean'' flag is specified. The target directory is recursively created if it is missing.\n"

        "$:/language/Help/server": {
            "title": "$:/language/Help/server",
            "description": "Provides an HTTP server interface to TiddlyWiki",
            "text": "The server built in to TiddlyWiki5 is very simple. Although compatible with TiddlyWeb it doesn't support many of the features needed for robust Internet-facing usage.\n\nAt the root, it serves a rendering of a specified tiddler. Away from the root, it serves individual tiddlers encoded in JSON, and supports the basic HTTP operations for `GET`, `PUT` and `DELETE`.\n\n```\n--server <port> <roottiddler> <rendertype> <servetype> <username> <password> <host> <pathprefix>\n```\n\nThe parameters are:\n\n* ''port'' - port number to serve from (defaults to \"8080\")\n* ''roottiddler'' - the tiddler to serve at the root (defaults to \"$:/core/save/all\")\n* ''rendertype'' - the content type to which the root tiddler should be rendered (defaults to \"text/plain\")\n* ''servetype'' - the content type with which the root tiddler should be served (defaults to \"text/html\")\n* ''username'' - the default username for signing edits\n* ''password'' - optional password for basic authentication\n* ''host'' - optional hostname to serve from (defaults to \"127.0.0.1\" aka \"localhost\")\n* ''pathprefix'' - optional prefix for paths\n\nIf the password parameter is specified then the browser will prompt the user for the username and password. Note that the password is transmitted in plain text so this implementation isn't suitable for general use.\n\nFor example:\n\n```\n--server 8080 $:/core/save/all text/plain text/html MyUserName passw0rd\n```\n\nThe username and password can be specified as empty strings if you need to set the hostname or pathprefix and don't want to require a password:\n\n```\n--server 8080 $:/core/save/all text/plain text/html \"\" \"\" 192.168.0.245\n```\n\nTo run multiple TiddlyWiki servers at the same time you'll need to put each one on a different port.\n"
        },
        "$:/language/Help/setfield": {
            "title": "$:/language/Help/setfield",
            "description": "Prepares external tiddlers for use",
            "text": "//Note that this command is experimental and may change or be replaced before being finalised//\n\nSets the specified field of a group of tiddlers to the result of wikifying a template tiddler with the `currentTiddler` variable set to the tiddler.\n\n```\n--setfield <filter> <fieldname> <templatetitle> <rendertype>\n```\n\nThe parameters are:\n\n* ''filter'' - filter identifying the tiddlers to be affected\n* ''fieldname'' - the field to modify (defaults to \"text\")\n* ''templatetitle'' - the tiddler to wikify into the specified field. If blank or missing then the specified field is deleted\n* ''rendertype'' - the text type to render (defaults to \"text/plain\"; \"text/html\" can be used to include HTML tags)\n"

\define slider(label,text)

<hr>

!!1) Buttons
Disable in Control panel (Appearance > Toolbars) the buttons you do not need in read-only mode.

''//Disable at least the following buttons://''

* ~ViewToolbar
** Edit button {{$:/core/images/edit-button}}
** More button {{$:/core/images/down-arrow}}
** Info button {{$:/core/images/info-button}} (Tools tab contains button configuration!)
* Page control buttons
** New tiddler button {{$:/core/images/new-button}}
** Control panel button {{$:/core/images/options-button}}
** Save button {{$:/core/images/save-button}}
** More button {{$:/core/images/down-arrow}}
<hr>

!!2) Sidebar tabs
Hiding tabs in the Sidebar is a 2-step procedure:<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;2a) Add the tag `$:/tags/hide` to tabs you want to manipulate.<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;2b)  Remove the tag `$:/tags/SideBar` from the tab you want to hide.

!!!2a) Add tag `$:/tags/hide`
Check the following for adding `$:/tags/hide`
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/SideBar]!tag[$:/tags/hide]sort[title]]"><br>
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/hide"> <$link to={{!!title}}><$view field="title"/>
</$link>
</$checkbox>
</$list>

Uncheck the following for removing `$:/tags/hide`
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/SideBar]tag[$:/tags/hide]sort[title]]"><br>
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/hide"> <$link to={{!!title}}><$view field="title"/>
</$link>
</$checkbox>
</$list>

!!!2b) Hide 'tabs in Sidebar'
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/hide]!tag[$:/tags/SideBar]sort[title]]"><br>
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/SideBar">&nbsp;&nbsp;Check to show <$link to={{!!title}}><$view field="title"/>
</$link>
</$checkbox>
</$list>
<$list filter="[all[shadows+tiddlers]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/hide]tag[$:/tags/SideBar]sort[title]]"><br>
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/SideBar">&nbsp;&nbsp;Uncheck to hide <$link to={{!!title}}><$view field="title"/>
</$link>
</$checkbox>
</$list>
<hr>

!!3) Hide Sidebar and Advanced search buttons
<<<
''Note:''<br>Although 'invisible' the buttons stay active!
<<<

!!!3a Sidebar button ({{$:/core/images/chevron-left}}/{{$:/core/images/chevron-right}})
 
<$list filter="[all[shadows]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/sidebar-button]!tag[$:/tags/Stylesheet]]">
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/Stylesheet">&nbsp;&nbsp;Check for 'invisible' buttons</$checkbox></$list>
<$list filter="[all[shadows]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/sidebar-button]tag[$:/tags/Stylesheet]]">
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/Stylesheet">&nbsp;&nbsp;Uncheck for visible buttons</$checkbox></$list>

!!!3b Advanced search button {{$:/core/images/advanced-search-button}}

<$list filter="[all[shadows]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/advanced-search-button]!tag[$:/tags/Stylesheet]]">
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/Stylesheet">&nbsp;&nbsp;Check for 'invisible' buttons</$checkbox></$list>
<$list filter="[all[shadows]!has[draft.of]tag[$:/tags/advanced-search-button]tag[$:/tags/Stylesheet]]">
<$checkbox tag="$:/tags/Stylesheet">&nbsp;&nbsp;Uncheck for visible buttons</$checkbox></$list>

!!4) Save (locally or to a server)
''{{$:/language/Buttons/SaveWiki/Hint}}'' {{$:/plugins/tongerner/ro/save-button}}

{{$:/core/ui/ControlPanel/Saving}}

A plugin to make ~TiddlyWiki read-only.

You can hide (at a minimum):

* ~ViewToolbar
** Edit button
* Page control buttons
** New tiddler button
** Control panel button
** Save button.

But you can hide as well:

* ''all'' other buttons
** 'Sidebar' button (to switch Sidebar) and 'Advanced search' button (next to Search) included
* ''all'' Sidebar tabs, even user added tabs.

Open [[$:/plugins/tongerner/ro/publish]] and follow the 4 steps.

<<<
''Note:''

* Although you can hide the 'Sidebar' and 'Advanced Search' button, they remain 'active'.
* Search in ''~AdvancedSearch'', tab ''Shadows'' for ''~ControlPanel'' to have access to:
** ''$:/ControlPanel > Appearance > Toolbars'' to unhide buttons
** ''$:/ControlPanel > Appearance > Publish'' to recover tabs, unhide buttons, ...
<<<

       
<$button message="tm-save-wiki" param={{$:/config/SaveWikiButton/Template}} tooltip={{$:/language/Buttons/SaveWiki/Hint}} aria-label={{$:/language/Buttons/SaveWiki/Caption}} class=<<tv-config-toolbar-class>>>
<span class="tc-dirty-indicator">
<$list filter="[<tv-config-toolbar-icons>prefix[yes]]">
{{$:/plugins/tongerner/ro/image-save-button}}
</$list>
<$list filter="[<tv-config-toolbar-text>prefix[yes]]">
<span class="tc-btn-text"><$text text={{$:/language/Buttons/SaveWiki/Caption}}/></span>
</$list>
</span>
</$button>

     display: none;

For certain\n * `font-size` values of the `input`, it causes the cursor style of the\n * decrement button to change from `default` to `text`.\n */\n\ninput[type=\"number\"]::-webkit-inner-spin-button,\ninput[type=\"number\"]::-webkit-outer-spin-button {\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n/**\n * 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome.\n * 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome\n *    (include `-moz` to future-proof).\n */\n\ninput[type=\"search\"] {\n  -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */\n  -moz-box-sizing: content-box;\n  -webkit-box-sizing: content-box; /* 2 */\n  box-sizing: content-box;\n}\n\n/**\n * Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari and Chrome on OS X.\n * Safari (but not Chrome) clips the cancel button when the search input has\n * padding (and `textfield` appearance).\n */\n\ninput[type=\"search\"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button,\ninput[type=\"search\"]::-webkit-search-decoration {\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n}\n\n/**\n * Define consistent border, margin, and padding.\n */\n\nfieldset {\n  border: 1px solid #c0c0c0;\n  margin: 0 2px;\n  padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em;\n}\n\n/**\n * 1. Correct `color` not being inherited in IE 8/9.\n * 2. Remove padding so people aren't caught out if they zero out fieldsets.\n */\n\nlegend {\n  border: 0; /* 1 */\n  padding: 0; /* 2 */\n}\n\n/**\n * Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 8/9.\n */\n\ntextarea {\n  overflow: auto;\n}\n\n/**\n * Don't inherit the `font-weight` (applied by a rule above).\n * NOTE: the default cannot safely be changed in Chrome and Safari on OS X.\n */\n\noptgroup {\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n/* Tables\n   ========================================================================== */\n\n/**\n * Remove most spacing between table cells.\n */\n\ntable {\n  border-collapse: collapse;\n  border-spacing: 0;\n}\n\ntd,\nth {\n  padding: 0;\n}\n"

The youth "requires additional assistance" to __complete__ an educational program or to secure and hold employment as determined by the <<strex '<$transclude tiddler="LWDB QR" />' "LWDB." "x" "LWDB:" "hint">>5% <<strex '<$transclude tiddler="ISY QR" />' "ISY" "x" "ISY" "hint">>newly enrolled in a program year limitation, applies to this criterion. The "requires additional assistance" policy should be reasonable, quantifiable, and based on evidence that the specific characteristics of the youth identified in the policy, objectively requires additional assistance. (20 CFT 681.220; 681.310). This criterion should be used as a last resort for youth eligibility due to the 5% limitation. 






"Requires additional assistance" to enter or complete and educational program or to secure or hold employment, as determined by the LWDBThe "requires additional assistance" policy should be reasonable, quantifiable, and based on evidence that the specific characteristics of the youth identified in the policy objectively requires additional assistance. This criterion should be used as a last resort for youth eligibility due to the 5% limitation. 






!!Customer Module

<ul>
<li>Create a new customer record, including:</li>
<ul>
<li>Complete all green dotted fields in the ''Customer Detail'' window. Follow the guidelines for the [[Employability Profile|https://labor.ny.gov/workforcenypartners/osos/OSOS-Guide-Employability-Profile.pdf]]. Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>
<li>In the "//Work History//" tab create a new job entry with a Job Type of "Military" and test the six Dislocated Worker categories under Reason for Leaving. (see [[OSOS-463]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
<li>Record all 1st, 2nd and 3rd RESEA  Activites, add one test comment.</li>
<li>Record all 1st, 2nd, and 3rd C3E Activities, add one test comment.</li>
<li> Add and complete a Work Search Plan. Attempt to download (export) the plan in all three formats (html, pdf, and doc).</li>
<li>Test the "Individual with Disability button/fields in the Work History tab (see [[OSOS-453i]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
</ul>
<li>Conduct a customer search (Customer Search window) for the newly created records</li>
<li>Conduct a general customer search (Customer Search window) that returns multiple search results. Attempt to export the search results.</li>
<li>Test that creation of OSOS record creates JZ record.</li>
</ul>

<ol>

<li>Customer Module>Customer Detail>Work History Tab - When Category 5 DW is selected, in TAA/NAFTA - TAA section, Qualifying Separation Date is required but has no green dot.</li>
</ol>

# English language learner;

!!Job Zone

* Create JZ account and see if it creates an OSOS SS/IO record
*Create a Work Search record. View and test the tabs of the Work Search Record - add employer contacts/activities.
* Export the Work Search Record in each format.
* Create Job Scout
* Create resume
* Upload external resume/work search record
* Conduct a keyword search (with or without an attached resume) 
* Conduct a resume-based job match. Determine if the search results are relevant to the information provided on the resume.







Relevant front-end bug fixes to be tested






!!Employer module  

* Correspondence
* Create new employer, employer contact, comments and due diligence
* Conduct an Employer Search for the newly created record
* Change data fields for existing employer, employer contact, comments and due diligence
* Enter employer Activities
* Delete employer Activities
* Create new job order
* Open a closed job order and revise data fields
* Add a duplicate  a job order and then delete
* Perform a job order match 
* Perform a customer match






<ul>
<li>Create a new customer record, including:</li>
<ul>
<li>Complete all green dotted fields in the ''Customer Detail'' window. Follow the guidelines for the [[Employability Profile|https://labor.ny.gov/workforcenypartners/osos/OSOS-Guide-Employability-Profile.pdf]]. Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>

<li>Test the "Individual with Disability button/fields in the Work History tab (see [[OSOS-453i]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
</ul>

<li>Conduct a general customer search (Customer Search window) that returns multiple search results. Attempt to export the search results.</li>

Follow the guidelines for the [[Employability Profile|https://labor.ny.gov/workforcenypartners/osos/OSOS-Guide-Employability-Profile.pdf]]. Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>
<li>
<li>In the "//Work History//" tab create a new job entry with a Job Type of "Military" and test the six Dislocated Worker categories under Reason for Leaving. (see [[OSOS-463]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
<li>Record all 1st, 2nd and 3rd DVOP Activities, add one test comment.</li>In the "//Add'l Info//" tab, make select the option for a "Transitioning Veteran" and attempt to save. (See bug [[22003]]).</li>
<li> Add and complete a Work Search Plan. Attempt to download (export) the plan in all three formats (html, pdf, and doc).</li>
<li>Test the "Individual with Disability button/fields in the Work History tab (see [[OSOS-453i]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
</ul>
<li>Conduct a customer search (Customer Search window) for the newly created records</li>
<li>Attempt to change the veteran customer to a non-veteran or use "Not Disclosed."</li>
</ul> 

''Note'': you can use the same record, just edit the various statuses/fields such as Active Service, Transitioning, etc. 






The participant is considered an ISY if they are attending high school or post-secondary school (as defined by State law) ISY are eligible for WIOA Youth programs if they:

<ol>
<li>Are not younger than 14 at the time of enrollment;</li>
<li>Are not older than 21 at the time of enrollment;</li>
<li>Are a [[low-income]] individual; ''and''</li>
<li>Have one or more of these barriers to employment:</li>
<ol>
<li>Basic skills deficient;</li>
<li>English language learner;</li>
<li>Offender - youth is involved in any stage of juvenile or adult justice system;</li>
<li>Homeless or runaway, who meet the criteria defined in the [[McKinney-Vinto Homeless Assistance Act|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McKinney%E2%80%93Vento_Homeless_Assistance_Act]] or the [[Violence Against Women Act of 1994|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Violence_Against_Women_Act]]</li>
<li>Involved in any stage of the foster care system;</li>
<li>Pregnant or parenting, including non-custodial parents;</li>
<li>With a disability; or</li>
<li>Fall under the [[5% exception for ISY]] for ISY</li>
</ol>
</ol>







''I''n-''S''chool ''Y''outh

!!Staff Permissions

* Create a new staff account
* Modify an existing staff account
* Activate and inactivate an account
* Add, delete secondary offices for a staff person
* Change password
* Test that invalid passwords are rejected and an error message appears
* Test permission levels: select, update, insert, and delete
* Test Security tab permissions

[[John Tully]] to assist where needed







!!Customer Module

<ul>
<li>Create a new [[In-School Youth]] Customer record, including:</li>
<ul>
<li>Complete all green dotted fields in the ''Customer Detail'' window.  Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Complete all tabs in the ''Comp Assess'' window.</li>

To support PIRL reporting, several fields within Customer Detail and Comp Assessment are now green dot required and/or provide the option of selecting “Not Disclosed”. Two new Individual with Disability fields have been added and are accessible in popup within Work History. The Military Spouse Displaced Homemaker fields have been removed and is now a new Reason For Leaving domain value. A few Seeker Service Groups, Seeker Service Categories and a Seeker Service Type have been added for PIRL reporting. All references to “WIA” have been updated to “WIOA”.






Manually entered wages can now be added and maintained in a new Seeker Manual Wage table. This is accessible within the Employer Outcomes tab for authorized administrators. These wages will only be used in PIRL reporting if no other wages are available for that Employer ID/EIN and quarter. This information will not be in the Quarterly Earnings table.






Edit functionality is now available for Seeker Eligibility Data (SED) records for authorized administrators. This is accessible from the Service History tab for Activities, Job Referrals and Services. This is also available from the Program/Public Assistance popup for records associated to a SED. This feature will allow edits for the record’s effective date and will allow those edits to be updated on all SED records for the designated period of time.






Customer Work Histories are now allowed to have a Job Type of “Military” with any of the six Dislocated Worker categories in the Reason For Leaving field. Formerly, it only allowed Category 3 and 4 Dislocated Worker reasons.






The participant is considered an OSY if they are not attending any school (as defined by State law). OSY are eligible for Youth programs if they:

<ol>
<li>Are not younger than 16 at the time of enrollment;</li>
<li>Are not older than 24 at the time of enrollment; ''and''</li>
<li>Are and individual who is facing one or more of the following identified barriers to employment:</li>
<ol>
<li>High school dropout;</li>
<li>Within the age of compulsory school attendance, but has not attended school for at least the most recent school calendar year quarter;</li>
<li>Offender - youth involved in any stage of juvenile or adult justice system;</li>
<li>Homeless or runaway, who meet the criteria defined in the [[McKinney-Vinto Homeless Assistance Act|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/McKinney%E2%80%93Vento_Homeless_Assistance_Act]] or the [[Violence Against Women Act of 1994|https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Violence_Against_Women_Act]]</li>
<li>Pregnant or parenting, including non-custodial parents;</li>
<li>With a disability;</li>
<li>Low-income and is a recipient of a high school diploma or its equivalent, and is basic skills deficient;</li>
<li>Low-income and is a recipient of a high school diploma or its equivalent, and is an English language learner; or</li>
<li>Low-income and fall under the [[5% exception for OSY]].</li>
</ol>






!!Customer Module

<ul>
<li>Create a new [[In-School Youth]] Customer record, including:</li>
<ul>
<li>Complete all green dotted fields in the ''Customer Detail'' window.  Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Complete all tabs in the ''Comp Assess'' window.</li>
<li>Enter a Youth Service in the Services Widow>Services tab and attach it to WIOA Youth funding.</li>
</ul>
<li>Create a new [[Out-of-School Youth]] Customer record and follow all of the same steps (above)</li>
<li>Conduct a customer search (Customer Search window) for the newly created records</li>
</ul>

OSOS [[Version 6.7.3|aosos_v6.8.0.r1_readme.pdf]] has been installed in the OSOS Test environment https://osostest/osos.html (open in Internet Explorer). This version contains the major system changes that have been implemented as a result of the transition from WIA to WIOA. Our units will be testing OSOS and ~JobZone before this new version can be moved into the production environment. 

Please follow your testing assignments and fill out the OSOS testing form (attached in the email). If you find a potential problem (bug), please fill out the bug report (also attached in the email) and send it to me. If I am able to replicate the bug, I will then send it on to ITS to be reviewed. Please let me know if there are any questions. 

If you find a bug, check this list of [[bugs that have already been reported|Already Reported Bugs]]. I will update this as they come in so as not to report the same issues. 

Click on your name to see your testing assignment:

!!Customer Module

<ul>
<li>Create a new customer record, including:</li>
<ul>
<li>Complete all green dotted fields in the ''Customer Detail'' window. Follow the guidelines for the [[Employability Profile|https://labor.ny.gov/workforcenypartners/osos/OSOS-Guide-Employability-Profile.pdf]]. Where possible, test more than one option anywhere there is a drop down menu and save after changes are made.</li>
<li>Complete the new "//Eligibility//" tab, including additional fields that appear when "Disabled" is chosen in the Disability Info section and when "Yes" is chosen in the Migrant Info section.</li>
<li>In the "//Work History//" tab create a new job entry with a Job Type of "Military" and test the six Dislocated Worker categories under Reason for Leaving. (see [[OSOS-463]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
<li>Record all 1st, 2nd and 3rd RESEA  Activites, add one test comment.</li>
<li>Record all 1st, 2nd, and 3rd C3E Activities, add one test comment.</li>
<li> Add and complete a Work Search Plan. Attempt to download (export) the plan in all three formats (html, pdf, and doc).</li>
<li>Test the "Individual with Disability button/fields in the Work History tab (see [[OSOS-453i]]) of the [[6.7.2 Readme|AOSOS V6 7 2Readme.pdf]].</li>
</ul>
<li>Conduct a customer search (Customer Search window) for the newly created records</li>
<li>Conduct a general customer search (Customer Search window) that returns multiple search results. Attempt to export the search results.</li>
<li>Test that creation of OSOS record creates JZ record.</li>
</ul>
